commitmsg: Downgrade to ClojureScript 1.9.229 to avoid unknown issue when opening DBs. 0.0.9.
Copy Datomish's test_macros.cljc, because it's no longer exported.
Add a quick pointer to Datomish.
Bump Datomish dependency to get latest SQLite.

Wait for the server to start before proceeding with tests.

Without this change, some tests will fail with timing-related errors, like

   POST /v1/sessions/end 200 15.903 ms - 2

   FAIL in (test-visits) (at /Users/rnewman/moz/git/datomish-user-agent-service/target/test/cljs/core/async/impl/channels.js:195:22)
   expected: (clojure.core/= e__41737__auto__ nil)
     actual: (not (clojure.core/= #object[FetchError FetchError: request to http://localhost:3002/v1/sessions/start failed, reason: connect ECONNREFUSED 127.0.0.1:3002] nil))
   POST /v1/sessions/start 200 269.530 ms - 17

We might consider shifting this change into server.cljs.
Fix an error introduced in "Support a basic limit for <saved-pages-matching-string."
Listen on localhost only by default. (#5)
Use scalar find spec to simplify <find-title. Fixes #11.
Add LICENSE, update documentation, bump to 0.0.2.
Review comment: license and clean up bin/user-agent-service.

Add /query and /transact endpoints.

These offer raw access to the underlying Datomish knowledge base, so
I've elected not to put them in the /v1 namespace.
Implement User Agent Service WebSocket API.

Make /query consider :page/* and :save/*.

This requires two queries for now; in the future, we'll be able to do it
with `or-join`.

This is Node.js-only so we don't need to wrap the module.

That means we get source maps!  Unfortunately, they're not too useful in
go-blocks, but every little helps.
First attempt at bundling for Node.js.

Split server out of core.

The server will be consumed by the JavaScript library interface.
Converge star API to Tofino UA Service API.
Initial commit, lightly modified from `lein new figwheel`.
